feat(studio): @deskwork/studio Hono server + page render scaffolds

Severs the editorial review surface from Astro by standing up an
independent Hono web server that exposes the same JSON API and rough
HTML page shape audiocontrol's Astro routes provide today.

Per the plan, this commit lands the architecture (server, route
adapters, page render skeletons, in-process tests). Phase 4 ports
the audiocontrol UI assets (~5,000 lines of HTML/CSS/JS) into
public/ and replaces the page render scaffolds with full templates.

Added:
- packages/studio/src/server.ts — Hono entry. CLI: `deskwork-studio
  [--project-root <path>] [--port <n>]`. Defaults: cwd / 4321.
  Reads .deskwork/config.json on startup; routes share a {projectRoot,
  config} StudioContext.
- packages/studio/src/routes/api.ts — 6 route handlers, each a thin
  wrapper over @deskwork/core/review/handlers (handleAnnotate,
  handleListAnnotations, handleDecision, handleGetWorkflow,
  handleCreateVersion, handleStartLongform). Path shapes match
  audiocontrol's /api/dev/editorial-review/* routes byte-for-byte.
- packages/studio/src/pages/{dashboard,review,shortform}.ts —
  minimal page render functions. Each reads relevant data from disk
  (calendar, workflows, versions, annotations) and emits HTML with
  data embedded as `<script type="application/json">` for the client
  to hydrate. Phase 4 fills in the full audiocontrol templates.
- packages/studio/src/pages/layout.ts — shared HTML shell (replaces
  audiocontrol's `<BlogLayout>` Astro component).
- packages/studio/test/api.test.ts — 12 in-process integration tests
  using `app.fetch(new Request(...))`. No real port binding. Covers
  every route + the page renders + the / redirect.

Wired up:
- npm workspace @deskwork/studio added to root.
- Hono + @hono/node-server runtime deps.
- bin/deskwork-studio symlink (npm-workspaces creates it).

Bug-found-and-fixed: the server's "is this the entry module"
guard used `import.meta.url === \`file://\${process.argv[1]}\``,
which fails when the user invokes via the symlinked bin
(node_modules/.bin/deskwork-studio). Replaced with a
realpathSync(argv[1]) === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url) check —
resolves the symlink before comparing.

Verified end-to-end:
- 12/12 studio tests pass
- 126/126 core, 27/27 cli still pass (165/165 total)
- All three workspaces typecheck clean
- `deskwork-studio --project-root <tmp> --port 47321` boots, serves
  /dev/editorial-studio (200), /dev/editorial-review-shortform (200),
  /api/dev/editorial-review/workflow (404 on missing — correct), and
  / (302 → /dev/editorial-studio)

Note: The static file server emits a "public/ not found" warning
because Phase 4 hasn't created the directory yet. This is expected
and harmless — only /static/* asset requests fail; dynamic routes
work fine.

Next: Phase 4 ports the UI assets (audiocontrol's editorial-review-
client.ts ~1,609L, editorial-studio-client.ts ~643L, editorial-
review-editor.ts ~201L, editorial-review.css ~2,269L, editorial-
studio.css ~171L) and replaces the page render scaffolds with full
template ports.
